The paper deals with distributed computing on graphs, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also focuses on fundamental graph problems, such as PageRank and triangle enumeration, which are part of the field of Graph Theory and Combinatorics (cs.DS). The message-passing model used in the paper involves communication between machines, which is related to the field of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The information-theoretic approach used to establish lower bounds is related to the field of Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents algorithms for solving the graph problems, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
